<TITLE> African author Achebe celebrated at DU </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 30 (bdnews24.com)The English department of Dhaka University celebrated 50 years of the classic novel Things Fall Apart by legendary Nigerian author Chinua Achebe with a day long international literature conference titled "African literature in English." Dhaka University vice chancellor Dr SMA Fayez inaugurated the conference as chief guest. The VC lauded Achebe's focus on developing world issues through his writing, read throughout Africa and the world. The conference was attended by representatives from India and Kenya among others. A total of 25 articles on the author were read in five sessions. Dhaka Padatik, a leading theatre group, performed the drama The Trial of Mallam Iliar by Ghanaian dramatist Mohammad bin Abdallah. The play was directed by Salek Khan. bdn
